The paper deals with physical-layer security in a wireless network, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. However, based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the authors propose a new scheme for enhancing physical-layer security using interference cancellation and opportunistic antenna selection. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). These sub-categories are relevant because the paper also considers a heterogeneous cellular network with multiple base stations and users, and analyzes the tradeoff between security and reliability in terms of intercept probability and outage probability.
